     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "LindbladSupermap[{a, b1, b2, ...}] or LindbladSupermap[a, {b1, b2, ...}] \
represents the superoperator generating the Markovian quantum operation \
associated with the effective Hamiltonian a and the Lindblad operators b1, \
b2, .... LindbladSupermap[{a, None}] or LindbladSupermap[a, None] assumes \
that all Lindblad operators vanish. LindbladSupermap[{None, b1, b2, ...}] or \
LindbladSupermap[None, {b1, b2, ...}] assumes that the effective Hamiltonian \
vanishes, which is useful in the interaction picture. \
LindbladSupermap[...][\\[Rho]] transforms linear operator \\[Rho].", 
